\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tep1665703133631.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tep1665703133631.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tep1665703133631.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tep1665703133631\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tep1665703133631__ugettxt_403900\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get the contents of a message or help text.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"tep1665703133631__topic_d120671e1_d120672e1_d120673e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tep1665703133631_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tep1665703133631__codeblock_gbg_cp1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">long ugettxt (unsigned char* id_string, char* buffer, long max);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tep1665703133631__topic_d85777e1_d85778e1_d85779e1_d85780e1_d85781e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1010581e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"tep1665703133631__parml_md2_dp1_1wb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">id_string</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tep1665703133631__p_d120680e1_d120681e1_d120682e1\">The ID string of the message or help\n                     text.</p>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"tep1665703133631__parml_zmr_2p1_1wb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The contents of the message or help text</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The maximum number of characters to be copied to the buffer pointed to by\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var>. The size of the buffer should be at least\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var>+1 to accommodate the zero terminator character.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tep1665703133631__topic_d85782e1_d85783e1_d85784e1_d85785e1_d85786e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1010581e112\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ugettxt and ugettxtc</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__1\">\n&gt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__2\">The number of bytes copied into the buffer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__1\">\n0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__2\">An error occurred</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__1\">\n&lt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tep1665703133631__d5946e20__entry__2\">The negated number of bytes copied into the\n                        buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the\n                        field, and that you should call <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> to get additional\n                        data. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tep1665703133631__topic_d85792e1_d85793e1_d85794e1_d85795e1_d85796e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1010581e176\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tep1665703133631__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tep1665703133631__topic_d85797e1_d85798e1_d85799e1_d85800e1_d85801e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1010581e189\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tep1665703133631__p_d120707e1_d120708e1_d120709e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxt</code> moves the contents of the\n            specified Uniface 4GL message or help text to the specified buffer. If there is more\n            data available than the buffer can hold, <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxt</code> returns a negative\n            status. In this case, you must call <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> repeatedly to get\n            additional data, until <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> returns a positive status. Calling\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxt</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> is functionally similar to\n            using the ProcScript function <code class=\"ph codeph\">$text(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">id_string</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tep1665703133631__p_d120710e1_d120711e1_d120712e1\">This function and its companion\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> work very similar to the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code> /\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code> pair. A notable difference is that there is no such thing as\n            a bind name here. In fact, <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> does not have a parameter for the\n            ID string; it just reads from the same source as <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxt</code> does, so there\n            would be no need for a bind name anyway.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tep1665703133631__p_d120713e1_d120714e1_d120715e1\">Note also that there is no parameter for the\n            library that your message or help text resides in. You must specify this by setting\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">$variation</code> to the correct library in your application’s assignment\n            file.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tep1665703133631__section_p5g_kp1_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1010581e249\">Example:  ugettxt and ugettxtc</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example retrieves and prints the string value of the\n            message or help text whose <var class=\"keyword varname\">IdString</var> is contained in general register\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">$1</code>. To illustrate the use of repeated <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code>\n            calls, we read in small chunks and grow the buffer as necessary, in the same way as in\n            the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code> / <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code> example.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tep1665703133631_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tep1665703133631__codeblock_bv1_4p1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">EXPORT void TEST_UGETTXT ()\n{\n#define CHUNKSIZE 12\nchar id[51];\nlong len;\nchar* buf;\nlong totlen;\n\nugetregs(1, (unsigned char *)id, sizeof(id)-1);\nbuf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE);\n\nlen = ugettxt(id, buf, CHUNKSIZE);\ntotlen = abs(len);\n\nwhile ( len &lt; 0 )\n{\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE);\nlen = ugettxtc(buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE);\ntotlen += abs(len);\n}\n\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+1);\nbuf[totlen] = 0;\nu_printf(\"The content of id %s is : %s\\n\", id, buf);\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xdm1665703133890.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugettxtc</a><p>Get additional data from a Uniface message or help text.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ugettxt Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get the contents of a message or help text. Explain this code long ugettxt (unsigned char* id_string, char* buffer, long max); Copy Parameters id_string The ID string of the message or help text. buffer (Output) The contents of the message or help text max The maximum number of characters to be copied to the buffer pointed to by buffer . The size of the buffer should be at least max +1 to accommodate the zero terminator character. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ugettxt and ugettxtc Value Meaning >0 The number of bytes copied into the buffer 0 An error occurred <0 The negated number of bytes copied into the buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the field, and that you should call ugettxtc to get additional data. Use Library: yrtl Description ugettxt moves the contents of the specified Uniface 4GL message or help text to the specified buffer. If there is more data available than the buffer can hold, ugettxt returns a negative status. In this case, you must call ugettxtc repeatedly to get additional data, until ugettxtc returns a positive status. Calling ugettxt and ugettxtc is functionally similar to using the ProcScript function $text( id_string ) . This function and its companion ugettxtc work very similar to the ufget / ufgetc pair. A notable difference is that there is no such thing as a bind name here. In fact, ugettxtc does not have a parameter for the ID string; it just reads from the same source as ugettxt does, so there would be no need for a bind name anyway. Note also that there is no parameter for the library that your message or help text resides in. You must specify this by setting $variation to the correct library in your application’s assignment file. Example: ugettxt and ugettxtc The following example retrieves and prints the string value of the message or help text whose IdString is contained in general register $1 . To illustrate the use of repeated ugettxtc calls, we read in small chunks and grow the buffer as necessary, in the same way as in the ufget / ufgetc example. Explain this code EXPORT void TEST_UGETTXT () { #define CHUNKSIZE 12 char id[51]; long len; char* buf; long totlen; ugetregs(1, (unsigned char *)id, sizeof(id)-1); buf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE); len = ugettxt(id, buf, CHUNKSIZE); totlen = abs(len); while ( len < 0 ) { buf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE); len = ugettxtc(buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE); totlen += abs(len); } buf = realloc(buf, totlen+1); buf[totlen] = 0; u_printf(\"The content of id %s is : %s\\n\", id, buf); } Copy Related Links ugettxtc Get additional data from a Uniface message or help text. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}